claim.claim-text:
1. A nanostructure device, comprising:
a flexible substrate;
a monocrystalline semiconductor layer formed on the flexible substrate;
a plurality of parallel cracks formed in accordance with a crystal cleave plane in the semiconductor layer, the cracks being spaced apart by an intercrack distance as determined by applying a particular strain to form parallel structures; and
a dielectric material formed in the cracks between and over the parallel structures on the semiconductor layer.

10. A nanostructure device, comprising:
a flexible substrate;
a monocrystalline semiconductor layer formed on the flexible substrate;
a plurality of parallel cracks formed in accordance with two crystal cleave planes in the semiconductor layer, the cracks being spaced apart by intercrack distances in two dimensions as determined by applying a particular strain to form dot structures; and
a dielectric material formed in the cracks between and over the dot structures on the semiconductor layer.

19. A nanostructure device, comprising:
a flexible substrate;
a monocrystalline semiconductor layer formed on the flexible substrate;
a plurality of parallel nanowires extending along a crystal cleave plane in the semiconductor layer, the nanowires having a thickness and a width, the width including an intercrack distance determined in accordance with a particular strain applied to the semiconductor layer to form the cracks;
an oxide formed between and over the nanowires to passivate and isolate adjacent nanowires; and
an electronic device or photonic device formed on the nanowires.
